need to be explored.

118
00:05:05,300 --> 00:05:08,020
Why do these Chinese students have all these
hangups?

119
00:05:08,020 --> 00:05:12,200
One major part of that is the Chinese Students
and Scholars Association,

120
00:05:12,200 --> 00:05:15,140
which basically functions as the Chinese government's

121
00:05:15,140 --> 00:05:17,180
ears and eyes on campus.

122
00:05:17,180 --> 00:05:19,450
It's kind of like a frat?

123
00:05:19,450 --> 00:05:21,020
Not quite.

124
00:05:21,020 --> 00:05:23,040
It's a rich kid frat.

125
00:05:23,040 --> 00:05:25,320
I know how to handle these people.

126
00:05:34,940 --> 00:05:35,440
It’s locked.

127
00:05:35,440 --> 00:05:36,380
No one’s home.

128
00:05:38,380 --> 00:05:41,520
Is this a Communist Party or what?

129
00:05:46,540 --> 00:05:48,220
Well, they wouldn't let me in.

130
00:05:48,220 --> 00:05:49,820
Can you get me in?

131
00:05:49,820 --> 00:05:50,980
No.

132
00:05:51,140 --> 00:05:52,000
Why not?

133
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:53,940
Last time I interacted with them,

134
00:05:53,940 --> 00:05:57,120
they followed me and tried to kick me out
of the venue.

135
00:05:57,120 --> 00:05:58,460
What's their deal?

136
00:06:00,180 --> 00:06:01,960
I'm not really sure.

137
00:06:03,720 --> 00:06:06,640
Yeah, well they just saw me going in and followed
me

138
00:06:06,650 --> 00:06:09,620
and had people sit around me and my friend,

139
00:06:09,620 --> 00:06:11,670
and watched us for the whole evening.

140
00:06:11,670 --> 00:06:12,670
And then

141
00:06:12,670 --> 00:06:13,670
when we went to the bathroom,

142
00:06:13,670 --> 00:06:14,670
they followed us, too,

143
00:06:14,670 --> 00:06:16,220
and tried to have us kicked out.

144
00:06:16,400 --> 00:06:18,040
Why did the CSSA target you?

145
00:06:18,460 --> 00:06:20,860
I'd previously reported on and investigated

146
00:06:20,870 --> 00:06:22,700
their ties to the Chinese government,

147
00:06:22,700 --> 00:06:25,640
and also their attempts to censor free information

148
00:06:25,640 --> 00:06:28,580
critical of the Chinese government on campus.

149
00:06:28,580 --> 00:06:29,710
And for that reason,

150
00:06:29,710 --> 00:06:31,770
they're extremely hostile towards me.

151
00:06:31,770 --> 00:06:32,770
And is it just you,

152
00:06:32,770 --> 00:06:34,420
or do they harass other students?

153
00:06:35,180 --> 00:06:38,220
I was there with a friend who is a political
dissident from China,

154
00:06:38,220 --> 00:06:40,960
and they were definitely targeting him as
well.

155
00:06:40,960 --> 00:06:43,680
And I think it's not just something at this
university.

156
00:06:43,680 --> 00:06:44,680
It's not just

157
00:06:44,680 --> 00:06:48,840
the CSSA at ANU, it's CSSAs all across the
globe

158
00:06:49,780 --> 00:06:53,620
that would be willing to engage in these kinds
of activities.

159
00:06:54,220 --> 00:06:56,160
What are some of the ways the CSSA

160
00:06:56,160 --> 00:06:58,160
monitors Chinese students abroad?

161
00:06:58,160 --> 00:07:02,180
Well, it's believed they're in regular contact
with the embassy.

162
00:07:02,190 --> 00:07:06,270
There have been a couple of cases of Chinese
students

163
00:07:06,270 --> 00:07:11,400
or lecturers making comments in class critical
of the Chinese Communist Party,

164
00:07:11,400 --> 00:07:14,060
and then these comments being reported back
to the Chinese government.

165
00:07:14,060 --> 00:07:18,270
So, it's quite likely that CSSAs are involved
in those cases.

166
00:07:18,270 --> 00:07:23,840
How can we tell the CSSA to be cool and stay
the heck out of school?

167
00:07:23,840 --> 00:07:27,990
I think it's important for universities to
send a message to CSSAs

168
00:07:27,990 --> 00:07:30,120
that they're not ever going to be endorsed
by universities.

169
00:07:30,120 --> 00:07:33,600
They won't be allowed to use university facilities,
and the universities

170
00:07:33,600 --> 00:07:38,240
should really encourage alternative Chinese
Student Associations

171
00:07:38,240 --> 00:07:42,260
that don't have these kinds of intimate ties
with the Chinese government.

172
00:07:42,260 --> 00:07:45,000
So, how can Chinese students be encouraged

173
00:07:45,000 --> 00:07:47,190
to come out of their shell a bit more?

174
00:07:47,190 --> 00:07:49,510
Yeah, universities really need to make sure

175
00:07:49,510 --> 00:07:51,320
they're spread out across the university.

176
00:07:51,320 --> 00:07:52,410
That they don't form enclaves,

177
00:07:52,410 --> 00:07:57,110
that they have ample opportunities to interact
with non-Chinese students

178
00:07:57,110 --> 00:07:58,344
and really make the most of their experience.

179
00:07:58,344 --> 00:08:01,850
What you're saying is, we need to throw a
party?

180
00:08:01,850 --> 00:08:02,940
That's not what I meant.

181
00:08:03,520 --> 00:08:05,400
The mother of all parties.

182
00:08:06,300 --> 00:08:07,340
I'm on this.

